risky%20to%20bring%20the%20astronauts%20home%20on%20the%20craft.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pair%20are%20slated%20to%20return%20home%20on%20a%20SpaceX%20mission%20in%20March%2C%20according%20to%20NASA.%20By%20then%2C%20they%20will%20have%20spent%20about%2010%20months%20in%20space.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20extended%20stay%20has%20captured%20national%20attention%20and%20concern%2C%20including%20from%20Trump%20and%20Musk%2C%20the%20chief%20executive%20officer%20of%20SpaceX.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20in%20a%20post%20on%20Truth%20Social%20in%20January%20said%20that%20the%20administration%20of%20former%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20had%20%26quot%3Bvirtually%20abandoned%26quot%3B%20the%20pair.%20Musk%20has%20repeatedly%20stated%20that%20the%20astronauts%20had%20been%20left%20in%20space%20due%20to%20political%20reasons%2C%20and%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X%20in%20February%20said%20that%20he%20had%20offered%20to%20return%20the%20astronauts%20sooner.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EPrice%20was%20never%20even%20discussed!%20They%20flatly%20refused.%20We%20would%20have%20made%20it%20work%20within%20the%20annual%20budget.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20real%20issue%20is%20that%20they%20did%20not%20want%20positive%20press%20for%20someone%20who%20supported%20Trump.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThat's%20it.%20End%20of%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Elon%20Musk%20(%40elonmusk)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Felonmusk%2Fstatus%2F1892617681796264436%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EFebruary%2020%2C%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EPam%20Melroy%2C%20former%20NASA%20deputy%20administrator%20under%20Biden%2C%20told%20Bloomberg%20News%20in%20February%20that%20top%20NASA%20officials%20had%20never%20received%20such%20an%20offer%20from%20Musk.%20Wilmore%20said%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20he%20believed%20Musk%2C%20but%20that%20he%20didn't%20have%20the%20details%20to%20confirm%20his%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20no%20information%20on%20that%2C%20though%2C%20whatsoever%20-%20what%20was%20offered%2C%20what%20was%20not%20offered%2C%20who%20it%20was%20offered%20to%2C%20how%20that%20process%20went%2C%26quot%3B%20Wilmore%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20of%20us%20have%20the%20utmost%20respect%20for%20Mr.%20Musk%20and%20obviously%2C%20respect%20and%20admiration%20for%20our%20president%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Donald%20Trump%2C%26quot%3B%20Wilmore%20added.%20%26quot%3BWe%20support%20our%20nation%2C%20we%20support%20our%20nation's%20leaders%2C%20and%20we're%20thankful%20for%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWilliams%20pushed%20back%20on%20Musk's%20recent%20suggestion%20that%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20should%20be%20retired%20early%2C%20rather%20than%20at%20the%20end%20of%202030%2C%20as%20currently%20planned.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20say%20we're%20actually%20in%20our%20prime%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Williams%20said%20of%20the%20ISS%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20think%20that%20right%20now%20it's%20probably%20not%20the%20right%20time%20to%20say%2C%20'Quit.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20Williams%20and%20Wilmore%20have%20been%20quick%20to%20downplay%20concerns%20about%20their%20extended%20stay%20in%20orbit%2C%20Williams%20did%20acknowledge%20that%20it%20has%20taken%20a%20toll%20on%20people%20back%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20hardest%20part%20is%20having%20the%20folks%20on%20the%20ground%20have%20to%20not%20know%20exactly%20when%20we're%20coming%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3Ball%20of%20that%20uncertainty%2C%20I%20think%2C%20is%20probably%20the%20most%20difficult%20part.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%